ded range with a [[hipped roof]].  In the centre is a 19th-century porch with a gable forming a [[pediment]] over a doorway flanked by square columns with ball [[finial]]s, and the windows are [[sash window|sashes]].  In the right return is a doorway with [[monolithic architecture|monolithic]] [[jamb]]s, an arched head and [[spandrel]]s.{{sfnp|Historic England|1300368|ps=none}}\n|align=\"center\" {{Grade II colour}}|{{sort|c|II}}\n|-\n|27 and 29 Brookfoot Lane<br/><small>{{coord|53.70615|-1.80212|type:landmark|name=27 and 29 Brookfoot Lane}}</small>\n|{{centre|\u2014}}\n|align=\"center\"|1787\n|A house and a school, later two houses, they are in stone on a [[plinth]], with [[rustication (architecture)|rusticated]] [[quoin (architecture)|quoins]], a [[belt course|band]], and a stone slate roof.  There are two storeys, a symmetrical front of three [[bay (architecture)|bays]], and a single-storey outshut at the rear under a catslide roof.  In the middle bay are paired doorways with a central [[monolithic architecture|monolithic]] [[jamb]], and the windows are [[sash window|sashes]].  Above the doorways is a large inscribed tablet.{{sfnp|Historic England|1133859|ps=none}}\n|align=\"center\" {{Grade II colour}}|{{sort|c|II}}\n|-\n|Former Bethel Chapel<br/><small>{{coord|53.70130|-1.78086|type:landmark|name=Former Bethel Chapel}}</small>\n|[[File:Brighouse Bethel Chapel 009.jpg|70px|centre]]\n|align=\"center\"|1811\n|The former chapel is in stone on a [[plinth]], with [[rustication (architecture)|rusticated]] [[quoin (architecture)|quoins]], a [[frieze]], a [[cornice]] and blocking course, and a stone slate roof.  There are two storeys and a symmetrical front of three [[bay (architecture)|bays]].  The central doorway is arched, with a rusticated surround and a heavy cornice on [[corbel|consoles]], and the windows are [[sash window|sashes]] with [[architrave]]s and cornices.{{sfnp|Harman|Pevsner|2017|p=148|ps=none}}{{sfnp|Historic England|1314042|ps=none}}\n|align=\"center